    "summary": "With over 20 years of experience in public transport, IT, infra construction, and OEM high-end industry, I am a strategic industry architect at T-Systems Nederland B.V., a leading provider of innovative IT solutions and services. \n\nMy mission is to embed digital solutions and connect IT to the operation of public transport and logistics clients, ranging from road, rail, (air)ports, and urban transport. I leverage my expertise in asset, maintenance, and project management, as well as new business development, to deliver custom-built solutions that meet the needs and challenges of the transport and logistics sector. \n\nAs an independent business owner of Can Do Company, I also provide interim expertise on innovations, sales, project, and asset management for complex contracts in infra, telecom, IT, and electric engineering and contracting. I am a committed manager, a builder and expander, and a goal-driven commercial thinker, who strives to achieve the maximum with limited resources and expand the boundaries of business and people. I have extensive international experience in risk-based projects and asset management, and I am always eager to learn and apply new tools and techniques, such as BIM, agile, and design thinking.",
